# Claude Code Instructions for This Project

## CRITICAL: Mandatory Standards Compliance

This Laravel project MUST follow CETAM (Centro de Desarrollo Tecnológico Aplicado de México) coding standards.

### 🎯 Primary Directive

**ALWAYS consult the laravel-cetam-standards skill before writing any code.**

This skill contains comprehensive standards for:
- Database design and nomenclature (MySQL)
- Laravel coding conventions
- Blade template structure
- TailwindCSS usage guidelines
- API response formats
- CETAM design system (colors, buttons, layouts)

### ⚡ Quick Reference

**Before ANY code task:**
1. Read the relevant section from laravel-cetam-standards skill
2. Verify nomenclature follows conventions
3. Check that code placement is correct
4. Ensure English-only naming

### 🔑 Key Standards Summary

**Language:** English ONLY (code, comments, database objects)

**Database:**
- Tables: plural snake_case (users, orders)
- Columns: singular snake_case (user_id, first_name)
- Foreign keys: {table_singular}_id
- Booleans: is_* or has_* prefix

**Laravel:**
- Controllers: PascalCase + Controller (UserController)
- Models: PascalCase singular (User)
- Routes: kebab-case with /p/{proj-slug}/ prefix
- Methods: camelCase (getUserList)
- Variables: camelCase ()
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_ATTEMPTS)

**Code Style:**
- Maximum 120 characters per line
- PSR-12 compliance mandatory
- 4 spaces indentation (no tabs)
- Strong typing when possible
- PHPDoc for all public methods

**Architecture:**
- Strict MVC pattern
- Business logic in Services/Repositories
- NO business logic in controllers or views
- Controllers maximum 300 lines

**Frontend:**
- TailwindCSS utility classes ONLY (no custom CSS)
- CETAM color palette: blue (#1d4976), orange (#de5629), gray (#7b96ab)
- Responsive design with breakpoint prefixes
- Component-based Blade architecture

### 🚫 Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. ❌ Using Spanish in code or database
2. ❌ Placing business logic in controllers
3. ❌ Creating custom CSS files
4. ❌ Exceeding 120 character line length without justification
5. ❌ Missing PHPDoc comments
6. ❌ Incorrect nomenclature conventions
7. ❌ Not using snake_case for database objects
8. ❌ Using project code in class names (e.g., CSUserController is WRONG)

### 📋 Validation Checklist

Before completing ANY task, verify:

- [ ] All names are in English
- [ ] Correct nomenclature applied (snake_case, camelCase, PascalCase)
- [ ] Code follows PSR-12 standards
- [ ] Database follows 3NF normalization
- [ ] Foreign keys have ON UPDATE/ON DELETE clauses
- [ ] Controllers are RESTful and lean
- [ ] Views use only TailwindCSS utilities
- [ ] API responses use camelCase keys
- [ ] Documentation and comments present
- [ ] No line exceeds 120 characters (unless justified)

### 📚 Getting Detailed Information

For comprehensive specifications and examples:

**Database work:**
Read the database-standards reference from laravel-cetam-standards skill

**Laravel development:**
Read the laravel-standards reference from laravel-cetam-standards skill

### 🎨 CETAM Design System

**Colors:**
- Primary: bg-institucional-azul (#1d4976)
- Accent: bg-institucional-naranja (#de5629)
- Support: bg-institucional-gris (#7b96ab)

**Buttons:**
- Primary: Blue background
- Secondary: Gray background
- Destructive: Orange border, transparent background

**Typography:**
- Font: Sans-serif (font-sans)
- Base size: text-base (16px)
- Titles: text-xl (20px), font-bold

### 🔧 Project Identification

This project uses code: **VOLT** (2-4 letters)

**Usage:**
- Namespaces: Cetam\VOLT\Http\Controllers
- Routes: /p/volt/...
- Route names: volt.module.action

**NOT in class names!**

